X
\hat{\sigma_X}^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}{\dfrac{(X_i-\mu)^2}{n}}
E[\hat{\sigma_X}^2]=\dfrac{n-1}{n}\sigma_X^2
E[\hat{\sigma_X}^2]=\dfrac{1}{n}E[\sum_{i=1}^{n}{(X_i-\mu)^2}]
\dfrac{1}{n}(E[(X_1-\mu)^2]+E[(X_2-\mu)^2]\cdots E[(X_n-\mu)^2])
\mu
(X_i - \mu)^2 = X_i^2 - 2 X_i \mu + \mu^2
E[X_i^2]
E[X_i \mu]
E[\mu^2]
\mu
E[(X_i - \mu)^2] = \sigma^2
E[\hat{\sigma}_X^2] = \sigma^2
